      </div> 
    </header> 
    <hr> 
    <section class="nav-section"> 
      <nav class="main-nav" aria-label="Main navigation"> 
        <a href="/">Blog</a> 
        <a href="/#projects">Projects</a> 
        <a href="/about/">About</a> 
        <a href="/resume/">Resume</a> 
      </nav> 
    </section> 
    <article class="article-card"> 
      <header class="article-header"> 
        <h1>About Me</h1> 
        <div class="article-meta"> 
          <span class="article-date">📅 08 Aug 2021</span>  
        </div>  
      </header> 
      <img class="article-image" src={AboutHeroImage.src} alt="About Me"> 
      <div class="article-content">  

        <h1>About Me</h1>

        <p>
          Hi, I'm <strong>Kaybee</strong>, a technology professional based in Sweden with a passion for
          <strong>Cloud Computing, DevOps, Embedded Systems, and IoT.</strong>
        </p>

        <p>
          My career has been built around technology and solving problems for people. I started in
          IT Support, helping users troubleshoot technical issues and maintain reliable IT services.
          I later joined <strong>Booking.com</strong>, where I worked as a
          <strong>Customer Support Specialist</strong> before transitioning into a
          <strong>Development Support Specialist</strong>. In these roles, I collaborated closely with
          customers, developers, and internal teams to resolve complex technical issues, improve user
          experiences, and support software products used by millions of people worldwide.
        </p>

        <p>
          Today, I work as a <strong>Customer Operations Professional at IAR</strong>, a global leader in
          embedded development software. Although my current role is not an engineering position, working
          in an environment focused on embedded technologies has strengthened my interest in how software,
          hardware, and cloud platforms work together to build reliable and intelligent systems.
        </p>

        <p>
          Alongside my professional career, I'm actively transitioning into Cloud and DevOps Engineering
          through continuous learning and hands-on projects. I'm currently studying Cloud Engineering,
          preparing for the Linux Foundation Certified System Administrator (LFCS) certification, and
          building real-world projects using modern cloud technologies.
        </p>

        <h2>What I'm Building</h2>

        <p>
          My interests extend beyond traditional cloud infrastructure. I'm passionate about connecting
          embedded devices to cloud platforms, automating deployments, and developing intelligent IoT
          solutions capable of solving real-world problems.
        </p>

        <p>
          One of my long-term goals is to build cloud-connected products that combine embedded systems,
          edge computing, automation, and artificial intelligence to improve industries such as
          agriculture, manufacturing, and industrial automation.
        </p>

        <h2>Technologies I'm Learning</h2>

        <ul>
          <li>Linux System Administration</li>
          <li>Amazon Web Services (AWS)</li>
          <li>Docker & Containerization</li>
          <li>Kubernetes</li>
          <li>Git & GitHub</li>
          <li>GitHub Actions (CI/CD)</li>
          <li>Terraform (Infrastructure as Code)</li>
          <li>Bash & Python Automation</li>
          <li>Networking & Security</li>
          <li>Embedded Systems</li>
          <li>Internet of Things (IoT)</li>
          <li>Edge Computing</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Why This Blog Exists</h2>

        <p>
          This blog is my personal knowledge base and portfolio. I use it to document everything I learn,
          build, and discover—from Linux commands and cloud infrastructure to DevOps automation,
          embedded systems, and IoT projects.
        </p>

        <p>
          Rather than only sharing finished projects, I also write about the challenges, mistakes, and
          lessons learned throughout my journey. I believe the best way to learn technology is by building
          in public and sharing knowledge with others.
        </p>

        <blockquote>
          "Technology is most impactful when software, hardware, and people work together to solve
          meaningful problems."
        </blockquote>

        <p>
          Thank you for visiting my blog. Whether you're here to learn something new, follow my journey,
          or connect professionally, I hope you find something valuable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

  </section>

</Layout>
